<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-03-28T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-03-28T07:00:00-05:00" n="272" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/512: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-03-28T20:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">March 28,
                                        1927—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 28—6:40
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>273. Following telegram has been sent to American consul general, Hankow:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“March 28, 7 p.m. Legation has today addressed following
                                    communication to all American missions, companies and
                                    individuals in all districts of northern Honan south of Yellow
                                    River: ‘In view of the present civil warfare Legation earnestly
                                    advises all American citizens to withdraw from all districts of
                                    Honan south of Yellow River.’”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>